4423void ARMAsmParser::

4426 assert(Kind < CVT_NUM_SIGNATURES && "Invalid signature!");
4427 const uint8_t *Converter = ConversionTable[Kind];
4428 unsigned OpIdx;

4858 cvtMVEVMOVQtoDReg(Inst, Operands);
4859 break;
4860 case CVT_95_addNEONinvi8ReplicateOperands:

4862 break;
4863 case CVT_95_addFPDRegListWithVPROperands:

4865 break;
4866 case CVT_95_addFPSRegListWithVPROperands:

4868 break;
4869 case CVT_imm_95_2:

4871 break;
4872 case CVT_imm_95_3:
4873 Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(3));
4874 break;
4875 }
4876 }

6183 case ARMAsmParser::Match_WLSLabel:
6184 return "loop end is out of range or not a positive multiple of 2";
6185 default:
6186 return nullptr;
6187 }
6188}

6238
6239static MatchClassKind matchTokenString(StringRef Name) {
6240 switch (Name.size()) {
6241 default: break;
6242 case 1: // 6 strings to match.
6243 switch (Name[0]) {
6244 default: break;
6245 case '!': // 1 string to match.
6246 return MCK__EXCLAIM_; // "!"
6247 case '[': // 1 string to match.
6248 return MCK__91_; // "["
6249 case ']': // 1 string to match.
6250 return MCK__93_; // "]"
6251 case '^': // 1 string to match.
6252 return MCK__94_; // "^"
6253 case '{': // 1 string to match.
6254 return MCK__123_; // "{"
6255 case '}': // 1 string to match.
6256 return MCK__125_; // "}"
6257 }
6258 break;
6259 case 2: // 6 strings to match.
6260 switch (Name[0]) {
6261 default: break;
6262 case '#': // 2 strings to match.
6263 switch (Name[1]) {
6264 default: break;
6265 case '0': // 1 string to match.
6266 return MCK__HASH_0; // "#0"
6267 case '8': // 1 string to match.
6268 return MCK__HASH_8; // "#8"
6269 }
6270 break;
6271 case '.': // 4 strings to match.
6272 switch (Name[1]) {
6273 default: break;
6274 case '8': // 1 string to match.
6275 return MCK__DOT_8; // ".8"
6276 case 'd': // 1 string to match.
6277 return MCK__DOT_d; // ".d"
6278 case 'f': // 1 string to match.
6279 return MCK__DOT_f; // ".f"
6280 case 'w': // 1 string to match.
6281 return MCK__DOT_w; // ".w"
6282 }
6283 break;
6284 }
6285 break;
6286 case 3: // 8 strings to match.
6287 switch (Name[0]) {
6288 default: break;
6289 case '#': // 1 string to match.
6290 if (memcmp(Name.data()+1, "16", 2) != 0)
6291 break;
6292 return MCK__HASH_16; // "#16"
6293 case '.': // 7 strings to match.
6294 switch (Name[1]) {
6295 default: break;
6296 case '1': // 1 string to match.
6297 if (Name[2] != '6')
6298 break;
6299 return MCK__DOT_16; // ".16"
6300 case '3': // 1 string to match.
6301 if (Name[2] != '2')
6302 break;
6303 return MCK__DOT_32; // ".32"
6304 case '6': // 1 string to match.
6305 if (Name[2] != '4')
6306 break;
6307 return MCK__DOT_64; // ".64"
6308 case 'i': // 1 string to match.
6309 if (Name[2] != '8')
6310 break;
6311 return MCK__DOT_i8; // ".i8"
6312 case 'p': // 1 string to match.
6313 if (Name[2] != '8')
6314 break;
6315 return MCK__DOT_p8; // ".p8"
6316 case 's': // 1 string to match.
6317 if (Name[2] != '8')
6318 break;
6319 return MCK__DOT_s8; // ".s8"
6320 case 'u': // 1 string to match.
6321 if (Name[2] != '8')
6322 break;
6323 return MCK__DOT_u8; // ".u8"
6324 }
6325 break;
6326 }
6327 break;
6328 case 4: // 14 strings to match.
6329 if (Name[0] != '.')
6330 break;
6331 switch (Name[1]) {
6332 default: break;
6333 case 'f': // 3 strings to match.
6334 switch (Name[2]) {
6335 default: break;
6336 case '1': // 1 string to match.
6337 if (Name[3] != '6')
6338 break;
6339 return MCK__DOT_f16; // ".f16"
6340 case '3': // 1 string to match.
6341 if (Name[3] != '2')
6342 break;
6343 return MCK__DOT_f32; // ".f32"
6344 case '6': // 1 string to match.
6345 if (Name[3] != '4')
6346 break;
6347 return MCK__DOT_f64; // ".f64"
6348 }
6349 break;
6350 case 'i': // 3 strings to match.
6351 switch (Name[2]) {
6352 default: break;
6353 case '1': // 1 string to match.
6354 if (Name[3] != '6')
6355 break;
6356 return MCK__DOT_i16; // ".i16"
6357 case '3': // 1 string to match.
6358 if (Name[3] != '2')
6359 break;
6360 return MCK__DOT_i32; // ".i32"
6361 case '6': // 1 string to match.
6362 if (Name[3] != '4')
6363 break;
6364 return MCK__DOT_i64; // ".i64"
6365 }
6366 break;
6367 case 'p': // 2 strings to match.
6368 switch (Name[2]) {
6369 default: break;
6370 case '1': // 1 string to match.
6371 if (Name[3] != '6')
6372 break;
6373 return MCK__DOT_p16; // ".p16"
6374 case '6': // 1 string to match.
6375 if (Name[3] != '4')
6376 break;
6377 return MCK__DOT_p64; // ".p64"
6378 }
6379 break;
6380 case 's': // 3 strings to match.
6381 switch (Name[2]) {
6382 default: break;
6383 case '1': // 1 string to match.
6384 if (Name[3] != '6')
6385 break;
6386 return MCK__DOT_s16; // ".s16"
6387 case '3': // 1 string to match.
6388 if (Name[3] != '2')
6389 break;
6390 return MCK__DOT_s32; // ".s32"
6391 case '6': // 1 string to match.
6392 if (Name[3] != '4')
6393 break;
6394 return MCK__DOT_s64; // ".s64"
6395 }
6396 break;
6397 case 'u': // 3 strings to match.
6398 switch (Name[2]) {
6399 default: break;
6400 case '1': // 1 string to match.
6401 if (Name[3] != '6')
6402 break;
6403 return MCK__DOT_u16; // ".u16"
6404 case '3': // 1 string to match.
6405 if (Name[3] != '2')
6406 break;
6407 return MCK__DOT_u32; // ".u32"
6408 case '6': // 1 string to match.
6409 if (Name[3] != '4')
6410 break;
6411 return MCK__DOT_u64; // ".u64"
6412 }
6413 break;
6414 }
6415 break;
6416 case 5: // 1 string to match.
6417 if (memcmp(Name.data()+0, ".bf16", 5) != 0)
6418 break;
6419 return MCK__DOT_bf16; // ".bf16"
6420 }
6421 return InvalidMatchClass;
6422}

6424/// isSubclass - Compute whether \p A is a subclass of \p B.

7538
7539 case MCK_rGPR:
7540 switch (B) {
7541 default: return false;
7542 case MCK_GPRnopc: return true;
7543 case MCK_GPRwithAPSR_NZCVnosp: return true;
7544 case MCK_GPRwithAPSRnosp: return true;
7545 case MCK_GPRwithZRnosp: return true;
7546 case MCK_GPR: return true;
7547 case MCK_GPRwithAPSR: return true;
7548 case MCK_GPRwithZR: return true;
7549 }
7550
7551 case MCK_Reg120:
7552 return B == MCK_DTriple;
7553
7554 case MCK_Reg115:
7555 return B == MCK_DTriple;
7556
7557 case MCK_Reg108:
7558 switch (B) {
7559 default: return false;
7560 case MCK_Reg109: return true;
7561 case MCK_DTriple: return true;
7562 }
7563
7564 case MCK_Reg79:
7565 switch (B) {
7566 default: return false;
7567 case MCK_Reg80: return true;
7568 case MCK_DQuad: return true;
7569 }
7570
7571 case MCK_Reg46:
7572 switch (B) {
7573 default: return false;
7574 case MCK_Reg47: return true;
7575 case MCK_DPair: return true;
7576 }
7577
7578 case MCK_GPRnopc:
7579 switch (B) {
7580 default: return false;
7581 case MCK_GPR: return true;
7582 case MCK_GPRwithAPSR: return true;
7583 case MCK_GPRwithZR: return true;
7584 }
7585
7586 case MCK_GPRwithAPSR_NZCVnosp:
7587 return B == MCK_GPRwithAPSR;
7588
7589 case MCK_GPRwithZRnosp:
7590 return B == MCK_GPRwithZR;
7591
7592 case MCK_QQPR:
7593 return B == MCK_DQuad;
7594
7595 case MCK_Reg126:
7596 return B == MCK_DTripleSpc;
7597
7598 case MCK_Reg109:
7599 return B == MCK_DTriple;
7600
7601 case MCK_Reg80:
7602 return B == MCK_DQuad;
7603
7604 case MCK_Reg71:
7605 return B == MCK_DPairSpc;
7606
7607 case MCK_Reg47:
7608 return B == MCK_DPair;
7609
7610 case MCK_DPR_VFP2:
7611 switch (B) {
7612 default: return false;
7613 case MCK_DPR: return true;
7614 case MCK_FPWithVPR: return true;
7615 }
7616
7617 case MCK_QPR:
7618 return B == MCK_DPair;
7619
7620 case MCK_SPR_8:
7621 switch (B) {
7622 default: return false;
7623 case MCK_HPR: return true;
7624 case MCK_FPWithVPR: return true;
7625 }
7626
7627 case MCK_DPR:
7628 return B == MCK_FPWithVPR;
7629
7630 case MCK_HPR:
7631 return B == MCK_FPWithVPR;
7632 }
7633}

7635static unsigned validateOperandClass(MCParsedAsmOperand &GOp, MatchClassKind Kind) {
7636 ARMOperand &Operand = (ARMOperand &)GOp;
7637 if (Kind == InvalidMatchClass)
7638 return MCTargetAsmParser::Match_InvalidOperand;
7639
7640 if (Operand.isToken() && Kind <= MCK_LAST_TOKEN)
7641 return isSubclass(matchTokenString(Operand.getToken()), Kind) ?
7642 MCTargetAsmParser::Match_Success :
7643 MCTargetAsmParser::Match_InvalidOperand;
7644
7645 switch (Kind) {
7646 default: break;
7647 // 'AM2OffsetImm' class
7648 case MCK_AM2OffsetImm: {

10172 Features.set(Feature_HasAcquireReleaseBit);
10173 if (FB[ARM::FeatureMP])
10174 Features.set(Feature_HasMPBit);
10175 if (FB[ARM::FeatureVirtualization])
10176 Features.set(Feature_HasVirtualizationBit);
10177 if (FB[ARM::FeatureTrustZone])
10178 Features.set(Feature_HasTrustZoneBit);
10179 if (FB[ARM::Feature8MSecExt])
10180 Features.set(Feature_Has8MSecExtBit);
10181 if (FB[ARM::ModeThumb])
10182 Features.set(Feature_IsThumbBit);
10183 if (FB[ARM::ModeThumb] && FB[ARM::FeatureThumb2])
10184 Features.set(Feature_IsThumb2Bit);
10185 if (FB[ARM::FeatureMClass])
10186 Features.set(Feature_IsMClassBit);
10187 if (!FB[ARM::FeatureMClass])
10188 Features.set(Feature_IsNotMClassBit);
10189 if (!FB[ARM::ModeThumb])
10190 Features.set(Feature_IsARMBit);
10191 if (FB[ARM::FeatureNaClTrap])
10192 Features.set(Feature_UseNaClTrapBit);
10193 if (!FB[ARM::FeatureNoNegativeImmediates])
10194 Features.set(Feature_UseNegativeImmediatesBit);
10195 if (FB[ARM::FeatureSB])
10196 Features.set(Feature_HasSBBit);
10197 return Features;
10198}

10519 MnemonicTable[Mnemonic]);

10529 return LHS < RHS.getMnemonic();
10530 }
10531 bool operator()(const MatchEntry &LHS, const MatchEntry &RHS) {

10533 }
10534 };

15493
15494#include "llvm/Support/Debug.h"
15495#include "llvm/Support/Format.h"
15496
15497unsigned ARMAsmParser::
15498MatchInstructionImpl(const OperandVector &Operands,
15499 MCInst &Inst,
15500 SmallVectorImpl<NearMissInfo> *NearMisses,
15501 bool matchingInlineAsm, unsigned VariantID) {
15502 // Get the current feature set.
15503 const FeatureBitset &AvailableFeatures = getAvailableFeatures();
15504
15505 // Get the instruction mnemonic, which is the first token.
15506 StringRef Mnemonic = ((ARMOperand &)*Operands[0]).getToken();
15507
15508 // Process all MnemonicAliases to remap the mnemonic.
15509 applyMnemonicAliases(Mnemonic, AvailableFeatures, VariantID);
15510
15511 // Find the appropriate table for this asm variant.
15512 const MatchEntry *Start, *End;
15513 switch (VariantID) {
15514 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid variant!");
15515 case 0: Start = std::begin(MatchTable0); End = std::end(MatchTable0); break;
15516 }
15517 // Search the table.
15518 auto MnemonicRange = std::equal_range(Start, End, Mnemonic, LessOpcode());
15519
15520 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "AsmMatcher: found " <<
15521 std::distance(MnemonicRange.first, MnemonicRange.second) <<
15522 " encodings with mnemonic '" << Mnemonic << "'\n");
15523
15524 // Return a more specific error code if no mnemonics match.
15525 if (MnemonicRange.first == MnemonicRange.second)
15526 return Match_MnemonicFail;
15527
15528 for (const MatchEntry *it = MnemonicRange.first, *ie = MnemonicRange.second;
15529 it != ie; ++it) {
15530 const FeatureBitset &RequiredFeatures = FeatureBitsets[it->RequiredFeaturesIdx];
15531 bool HasRequiredFeatures =
15532 (AvailableFeatures & RequiredFeatures) == RequiredFeatures;
15533 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "Trying to match opcode "
15534 << MII.getName(it->Opcode) << "\n");
15535 // Some state to record ways in which this instruction did not match.
15536 NearMissInfo OperandNearMiss = NearMissInfo::getSuccess();
15537 NearMissInfo FeaturesNearMiss = NearMissInfo::getSuccess();
15538 NearMissInfo EarlyPredicateNearMiss = NearMissInfo::getSuccess();
15539 NearMissInfo LatePredicateNearMiss = NearMissInfo::getSuccess();
15540 bool MultipleInvalidOperands = false;
15541 // equal_range guarantees that instruction mnemonic matches.
15542 assert(Mnemonic == it->getMnemonic());
15543 for (unsigned FormalIdx = 0, ActualIdx = 1; FormalIdx != 18; ++FormalIdx) {
15544 auto Formal = static_cast<MatchClassKind>(it->Classes[FormalIdx]);
15545 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher",
15546 dbgs() << " Matching formal operand class " << getMatchClassName(Formal)
15547 << " against actual operand at index " << ActualIdx);
15548 if (ActualIdx < Operands.size())
15549 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << " (";
15550 Operands[ActualIdx]->print(dbgs()); dbgs() << "): ");
15551 else
15552 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << ": ");
15553 if (ActualIdx >= Operands.size()) {
15554 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "actual operand index out of range ");
15555 bool ThisOperandValid = (Formal == InvalidMatchClass) || isSubclass(Formal, OptionalMatchClass);
15556 if (!ThisOperandValid) {
15557 if (!OperandNearMiss) {
15558 // Record info about match failure for later use.
15559 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "recording too-few-operands near miss\n");
15560 OperandNearMiss =
15561 NearMissInfo::getTooFewOperands(Formal, it->Opcode);
15562 } else if (OperandNearMiss.getKind() != NearMissInfo::NearMissTooFewOperands) {
15563 // If more than one operand is invalid, give up on this match entry.
15564 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(
15565 "asm-matcher",
15566 dbgs() << "second invalid operand, giving up on this opcode\n");
15567 MultipleInvalidOperands = true;
15568 break;
15569 }
15570 } else {
15571 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "but formal operand not required\n");
15572 break;
15573 }
15574 continue;
15575 }
15576 MCParsedAsmOperand &Actual = *Operands[ActualIdx];
15577 unsigned Diag = validateOperandClass(Actual, Formal);
15578 if (Diag == Match_Success) {
15579 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher",
15580 dbgs() << "match success using generic matcher\n");
15581 ++ActualIdx;
15582 continue;
15583 }
15584 // If the generic handler indicates an invalid operand
15585 // failure, check for a special case.
15586 if (Diag != Match_Success) {
15587 unsigned TargetDiag = validateTargetOperandClass(Actual, Formal);
15588 if (TargetDiag == Match_Success) {
15589 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher",
15590 dbgs() << "match success using target matcher\n");
15591 ++ActualIdx;
15592 continue;
15593 }
15594 // If the target matcher returned a specific error code use
15595 // that, else use the one from the generic matcher.
15596 if (TargetDiag != Match_InvalidOperand && HasRequiredFeatures)
15597 Diag = TargetDiag;
15598 }
15599 // If current formal operand wasn't matched and it is optional
15600 // then try to match next formal operand
15601 if (Diag == Match_InvalidOperand && isSubclass(Formal, OptionalMatchClass)) {
15602 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "ignoring optional operand\n");
15603 continue;
15604 }
15605 if (!OperandNearMiss) {
15606 // If this is the first invalid operand we have seen, record some
15607 // information about it.
15608 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(
15609 "asm-matcher",
15610 dbgs()
15611 << "operand match failed, recording near-miss with diag code "
15612 << Diag << "\n");
15613 OperandNearMiss =
15614 NearMissInfo::getMissedOperand(Diag, Formal, it->Opcode, ActualIdx);
15615 ++ActualIdx;
15616 } else {
15617 // If more than one operand is invalid, give up on this match entry.
15618 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(
15619 "asm-matcher",
15620 dbgs() << "second operand mismatch, skipping this opcode\n");
15621 MultipleInvalidOperands = true;
15622 break;
15623 }
15624 }
15625
15626 if (MultipleInvalidOperands) {
15627 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "Opcode result: multiple "
15628 "operand mismatches, ignoring "
15629 "this opcode\n");
15630 continue;
15631 }
15632 if (!HasRequiredFeatures) {
15633 FeatureBitset NewMissingFeatures = RequiredFeatures & ~AvailableFeatures;
15634 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "Missing target features:";
15635 for (unsigned I = 0, E = NewMissingFeatures.size(); I != E; ++I)
15636 if (NewMissingFeatures[I])
15637 dbgs() << ' ' << I;
15638 dbgs() << "\n");
15639 FeaturesNearMiss = NearMissInfo::getMissedFeature(NewMissingFeatures);
15640 }
15641
15642 Inst.clear();
15643
15644 Inst.setOpcode(it->Opcode);
15645 // We have a potential match but have not rendered the operands.
15646 // Check the target predicate to handle any context sensitive
15647 // constraints.
15648 // For example, Ties that are referenced multiple times must be
15649 // checked here to ensure the input is the same for each match
15650 // constraints. If we leave it any later the ties will have been
15651 // canonicalized
15652 unsigned MatchResult;
15653 if ((MatchResult = checkEarlyTargetMatchPredicate(Inst, Operands)) != Match_Success) {
15654 Inst.clear();
15655 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(
15656 "asm-matcher",
15657 dbgs() << "Early target match predicate failed with diag code "
15658 << MatchResult << "\n");
15659 EarlyPredicateNearMiss = NearMissInfo::getMissedPredicate(MatchResult);
15660 }
15661
15662 // If we did not successfully match the operands, then we can't convert to
15663 // an MCInst, so bail out on this instruction variant now.
15664 if (OperandNearMiss) {
15665 // If the operand mismatch was the only problem, reprrt it as a near-miss.
15666 if (NearMisses && !FeaturesNearMiss && !EarlyPredicateNearMiss) {
15667 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(
15668 "asm-matcher",
15669 dbgs()
15670 << "Opcode result: one mismatched operand, adding near-miss\n");
15671 NearMisses->push_back(OperandNearMiss);
15672 } else {
15673 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "Opcode result: multiple "
15674 "types of mismatch, so not "
15675 "reporting near-miss\n");
15676 }
15677 continue;
15678 }
15679
15680 if (matchingInlineAsm) {
15681 convertToMapAndConstraints(it->ConvertFn, Operands);
15682 return Match_Success;
15683 }
15684
15685 // We have selected a definite instruction, convert the parsed
15686 // operands into the appropriate MCInst.
15687 convertToMCInst(it->ConvertFn, Inst, it->Opcode, Operands);
15688
15689 // We have a potential match. Check the target predicate to
15690 // handle any context sensitive constraints.
15691 if ((MatchResult = checkTargetMatchPredicate(Inst)) != Match_Success) {
15692 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher",
15693 dbgs() << "Target match predicate failed with diag code "
15694 << MatchResult << "\n");
15695 Inst.clear();
15696 LatePredicateNearMiss = NearMissInfo::getMissedPredicate(MatchResult);
15697 }
15698
15699 int NumNearMisses = ((int)(bool)OperandNearMiss +
15700 (int)(bool)FeaturesNearMiss +
15701 (int)(bool)EarlyPredicateNearMiss +
15702 (int)(bool)LatePredicateNearMiss);
15703 if (NumNearMisses == 1) {
15704 // We had exactly one type of near-miss, so add that to the list.
15705 assert(!OperandNearMiss && "OperandNearMiss was handled earlier");
15706 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "Opcode result: found one type of "
15707 "mismatch, so reporting a "
15708 "near-miss\n");
15709 if (NearMisses && FeaturesNearMiss)
15710 NearMisses->push_back(FeaturesNearMiss);
15711 else if (NearMisses && EarlyPredicateNearMiss)
15712 NearMisses->push_back(EarlyPredicateNearMiss);
15713 else if (NearMisses && LatePredicateNearMiss)
15714 NearMisses->push_back(LatePredicateNearMiss);
15715
15716 continue;
15717 } else if (NumNearMisses > 1) {
15718 // This instruction missed in more than one way, so ignore it.
15719 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE("asm-matcher", dbgs() << "Opcode result: multiple "
15720 "types of mismatch, so not "
15721 "reporting near-miss\n");
15722 continue;
15723 }
15724 std::string Info;
15725 if (!getParser().getTargetParser().
15726 getTargetOptions().MCNoDeprecatedWarn &&
15727 MII.getDeprecatedInfo(Inst, getSTI(), Info)) {
15728 SMLoc Loc = ((ARMOperand &)*Operands[0]).getStartLoc();
15729 getParser().Warning(Loc, Info, None);
15730 }
15731 DEBUG_WITH_TYPE(
15732 "asm-matcher",
15733 dbgs() << "Opcode result: complete match, selecting this opcode\n");
15734 return Match_Success;
15735 }
15736
15737 // No instruction variants matched exactly.
15738 return Match_NearMisses;
15739}
15740
15741namespace {
15742 struct OperandMatchEntry {
15743 uint16_t Mnemonic;
15744 uint8_t OperandMask;
15745 uint16_t Class;
15746 uint8_t RequiredFeaturesIdx;
15747
15748 StringRef getMnemonic() const {
15749 return StringRef(MnemonicTable + Mnemonic + 1,
15750 MnemonicTable[Mnemonic]);
15751 }
15752 };
15753
15754 // Predicate for searching for an opcode.
15755 struct LessOpcodeOperand {
15756 bool operator()(const OperandMatchEntry &LHS, StringRef RHS) {
15757 return LHS.getMnemonic() < RHS;
15758 }
15759 bool operator()(StringRef LHS, const OperandMatchEntry &RHS) {
15760 return LHS < RHS.getMnemonic();
15761 }
15762 bool operator()(const OperandMatchEntry &LHS, const OperandMatchEntry &RHS) {
15763 return LHS.getMnemonic() < RHS.getMnemonic();
15764 }
15765 };
15766} // end anonymous namespace

16677 return parseCoprocOptionOperand(Operands);

16680 case MCK_FPImm:

16693 return parsePKHLSLImm(Operands);
16694 case MCK_PostIdxReg:
16695 return parsePostIdxReg(Operands);
16696 case MCK_PostIdxRegShifted:

16795
16796OperandMatchResultTy ARMAsmParser::
16797MatchOperandParserImpl(OperandVector &Operands,
16798 StringRef Mnemonic,
16799 bool ParseForAllFeatures) {
16800 // Get the current feature set.
16801 const FeatureBitset &AvailableFeatures = getAvailableFeatures();
16802
16803 // Get the next operand index.
16804 unsigned NextOpNum = Operands.size() - 1;
16805 // Search the table.
16806 auto MnemonicRange =
16807 std::equal_range(std::begin(OperandMatchTable), std::end(OperandMatchTable),
16808 Mnemonic, LessOpcodeOperand());
16809
16810 if (MnemonicRange.first == MnemonicRange.second)
16811 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
16812
16813 for (const OperandMatchEntry *it = MnemonicRange.first,
16814 *ie = MnemonicRange.second; it != ie; ++it) {
16815 // equal_range guarantees that instruction mnemonic matches.
16816 assert(Mnemonic == it->getMnemonic());
16817
16818 // check if the available features match
16819 const FeatureBitset &RequiredFeatures = FeatureBitsets[it->RequiredFeaturesIdx];
16820 if (!ParseForAllFeatures && (AvailableFeatures & RequiredFeatures) != RequiredFeatures)
16821 continue;
16822
16823 // check if the operand in question has a custom parser.
16824 if (!(it->OperandMask & (1 << NextOpNum)))
16825 continue;
16826
16827 // call custom parse method to handle the operand
16828 OperandMatchResultTy Result = tryCustomParseOperand(Operands, it->Class);
16829 if (Result != MatchOperand_NoMatch)
16830 return Result;
16831 }
16832
16833 // Okay, we had no match.
16834 return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
16835}
16836
16837#endif // GET_MATCHER_IMPLEMENTATION
16838
16839
16840#ifdef GET_MNEMONIC_SPELL_CHECKER
16841#undef GET_MNEMONIC_SPELL_CHECKER
16842
16843static std::string ARMMnemonicSpellCheck(StringRef S, const FeatureBitset &FBS, unsigned VariantID) {
16844 const unsigned MaxEditDist = 2;
16845 std::vector<StringRef> Candidates;
16846 StringRef Prev = "";
16847
16848 // Find the appropriate table for this asm variant.
16849 const MatchEntry *Start, *End;
16850 switch (VariantID) {
16851 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid variant!");
16852 case 0: Start = std::begin(MatchTable0); End = std::end(MatchTable0); break;
16853 }
16854
16855 for (auto I = Start; I < End; I++) {
16856 // Ignore unsupported instructions.
16857 const FeatureBitset &RequiredFeatures = FeatureBitsets[I->RequiredFeaturesIdx];
16858 if ((FBS & RequiredFeatures) != RequiredFeatures)
16859 continue;
16860
16861 StringRef T = I->getMnemonic();
16862 // Avoid recomputing the edit distance for the same string.
16863 if (T.equals(Prev))
16864 continue;
16865
16866 Prev = T;
16867 unsigned Dist = S.edit_distance(T, false, MaxEditDist);
16868 if (Dist <= MaxEditDist)
16869 Candidates.push_back(T);
16870 }
16871
16872 if (Candidates.empty())
16873 return "";
16874
16875 std::string Res = ", did you mean: ";
16876 unsigned i = 0;
16877 for (; i < Candidates.size() - 1; i++)
16878 Res += Candidates[i].str() + ", ";
16879 return Res + Candidates[i].str() + "?";
16880}
16881
16882#endif // GET_MNEMONIC_SPELL_CHECKER
16883
16884
16885#ifdef GET_MNEMONIC_CHECKER
16886#undef GET_MNEMONIC_CHECKER
16887
16888static bool ARMCheckMnemonic(StringRef Mnemonic,
16889 const FeatureBitset &AvailableFeatures,
16890 unsigned VariantID) {
16891 // Process all MnemonicAliases to remap the mnemonic.
16892 applyMnemonicAliases(Mnemonic, AvailableFeatures, VariantID);
16893
16894 // Find the appropriate table for this asm variant.
16895 const MatchEntry *Start, *End;
16896 switch (VariantID) {
16897 default: llvm_unreachable("invalid variant!");
16898 case 0: Start = std::begin(MatchTable0); End = std::end(MatchTable0); break;
16899 }
16900
16901 // Search the table.
16902 auto MnemonicRange = std::equal_range(Start, End, Mnemonic, LessOpcode());
16903
16904 if (MnemonicRange.first == MnemonicRange.second)
16905 return false;
16906
16907 for (const MatchEntry *it = MnemonicRange.first, *ie = MnemonicRange.second;
16908 it != ie; ++it) {
16909 const FeatureBitset &RequiredFeatures =
16910 FeatureBitsets[it->RequiredFeaturesIdx];
16911 if ((AvailableFeatures & RequiredFeatures) == RequiredFeatures)
16912 return true;
16913 }
16914 return false;
16915}

16917#endif // GET_MNEMONIC_CHECKER
